---
// src/pages/civil/cee335l/day1.astro
const title = "Day 1 — ETABS Introduction & Environment Setup";
const description = "Get ETABS running, understand the interface, and build your first simple model. The foundation for everything that follows.";
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>{title} | CEE335L | Mathify</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description} />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=Playfair+Display:wght@700;900&family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

  <style>
    :root {
      --bg:      #0d0d0f;
      --bg2:     #13131a;
      --bg3:     #1a1a24;
      --border:  #2a2a3a;
      --text:    #e8e8f0;
      --muted:   #7a7a9a;
      --accent:  #f0a500;
      --accent2: #3ecfcf;
      --accent3: #e05c5c;
      --green:   #4ade80;
      --mono:    'Space Mono', monospace;
      --serif:   'Playfair Display', serif;
      --sans:    'Inter', sans-serif;
    }
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
    body { background: var(--bg); color: var(--text); font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: hidden; }

    /* NAV */
    nav {
      position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100;
      background: rgba(13,13,15,0.92); backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 0.75rem 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 2rem;
    }
    .nav-logo { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1rem; color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
    .nav-links { display: flex; gap: 1.5rem; list-style: none; }
    .nav-links a { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 0.05em; transition: color 0.2s; }
    .nav-links a:hover { color: var(--text); }
    .breadcrumb { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted); margin-left: auto; letter-spacing: 0.08em; }
    .breadcrumb a { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; }
    .breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

    /* HERO */
    .hero {
      padding: 4rem 2rem 3rem; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .day-tag {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--accent2);
      letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .day-tag::before { content: ''; width: 2rem; height: 1px; background: var(--accent2); }
    .hero h1 {
      font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
      font-weight: 900; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .hero h1 span { color: var(--accent); }
    .hero-sub { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--muted); max-width: 580px; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .badge-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.6rem; }
    .badge {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      padding: 0.28rem 0.7rem; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid;
    }
    .badge-amber  { color: var(--accent);  border-color: var(--accent);  background: rgba(240,165,0,0.08); }
    .badge-teal   { color: var(--accent2); border-color: var(--accent2); background: rgba(62,207,207,0.08); }
    .badge-green  { color: var(--green);   border-color: var(--green);   background: rgba(74,222,128,0.08); }

    /* SECTION */
    .section { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3.5rem 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
    .section-num {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--accent);
      letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    .section-num::after { content: ''; flex: 0 0 3rem; height: 1px; background: var(--border); }
    .section h2 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 3vw, 1.9rem); font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .section-intro { color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; max-width: 620px; }

    /* CONTENT PLACEHOLDER */
    .coming-soon {
      background: var(--bg2); border: 1px dashed var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px; padding: 2rem; text-align: center;
      color: var(--muted); font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.8rem;
    }
    .coming-soon strong { color: var(--accent); display: block; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

    /* STEP CARDS */
    .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }
    .step-card {
      background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
      display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; align-items: flex-start;
    }
    .step-num {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--accent);
      font-weight: 700; min-width: 2rem; line-height: 1.4;
    }
    .step-body h4 { font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .step-body p  { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--muted); }

    /* DAY NAV */
    .day-nav {
      max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 2rem 3rem;
      display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .nav-btn {
      font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 6px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border); background: var(--bg2);
      color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none;
      transition: all 0.2s; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .nav-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .nav-btn.next { background: rgba(240,165,0,0.08); border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }
    .nav-btn.next:hover { background: rgba(240,165,0,0.15); }
    .day-center { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--muted); letter-spacing: 0.1em; }

    /* UTIL */
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      nav { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
      .hero, .section { padding-left: 1.25rem; padding-right: 1.25rem; }
      .day-nav { padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem 2.5rem; }
    }
    ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; } ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--bg); } ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); border-radius: 3px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<nav>
  <a href="/" class="nav-logo">mathify</a>
  <ul class="nav-links">
    <li><a href="/math">Math</a></li>
    <li><a href="/physics">Physics</a></li>
    <li><a href="/civil">Civil</a></li>
  </ul>
  <span class="breadcrumb">
    <a href="/civil">Civil</a> ›
    <a href="/civil/cee335l/">CEE335L</a> › Day 1
  </span>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<header class="hero">
  <div class="day-tag">Day 1 of 11 — Class 1</div>
  <h1>ETABS Introduction &amp;<br><span>Environment Setup</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-sub">
    Orient yourself to the software. Understand the ETABS workspace, units, grids, and how structural models are assembled from elements.
  </p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="badge badge-amber">ETABS</span>
    <span class="badge badge-teal">Interface</span>
    <span class="badge badge-teal">Units & Grid</span>
    <span class="badge badge-green">First Model</span>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- 01: WHY -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">01 — Why</div>
  <h2>Why does the interface matter before the analysis?</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    Every ETABS error traced back to a modelling mistake — wrong units, missing constraints, bad grid spacing.
    Getting comfortable with the workspace on Day 1 prevents two weeks of debugging later.
  </p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Content Coming Soon</strong>
    Intuition hook — why structural software literacy is now a hiring requirement, and what ETABS does that hand calc cannot.
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02: CONCEPT -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">02 — Concept</div>
  <h2>How ETABS thinks about a structure</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">
    ETABS represents structures as a system of nodes, frames (beams/columns), shells (slabs/walls), and loads — all connected through a stiffness matrix. Here's the mental model.
  </p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Content Coming Soon</strong>
    FEM primer: nodes, elements, DOFs, stiffness matrix intuition. No math — just the concept.
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03: WALKTHROUGH -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">03 — Walkthrough</div>
  <h2>Step-by-step: Day 1 in ETABS</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Follow these steps exactly as covered in class. Check each one off as you go.</p>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">01</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Open ETABS and set units</h4>
        <p>File → New Model. Set units to kN–m or kip–ft depending on the problem. Units cannot be changed mid-model without rechecking all loads.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">02</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Define the grid system</h4>
        <p>Edit → Edit Grid Data. Set X and Y spacings to match your structural bay layout. Z levels define each floor.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">03</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Define materials</h4>
        <p>Define → Materials. Add concrete (f'c) and steel (fy). ETABS ships with defaults — verify they match your code (ACI / BNBC).</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">04</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Define frame sections</h4>
        <p>Define → Section Properties → Frame Sections. Create rectangular beam and column sections. Assign the material you just defined.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card">
      <div class="step-num">05</div>
      <div class="step-body">
        <h4>Draw frames & run a test analysis</h4>
        <p>Draw → Draw Frame/Cable/Tendon. Place columns at grid intersections, beams along spans. Assign → Frame Loads → Add a dummy load. Analyze → Run.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04: CHECK -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="section-num">04 — Check Yourself</div>
  <h2>Quick-check questions</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Answer these before moving to Day 2.</p>
  <div class="coming-soon">
    <strong>Interactive Quiz Coming Soon</strong>
    5-question multiple choice covering: unit systems, ETABS element types, DOF constraints, material definition, and analysis types (linear static vs. modal).
  </div>
</section>

<!-- DAY NAV -->
<nav class="day-nav">
  <a href="/civil/cee335l/" class="nav-btn">← Course Index</a>
  <span class="day-center">CEE335L · Day 1 / 11</span>
  <a href="/civil/cee335l/day2" class="nav-btn next">Day 2 →</a>
</nav>

</body>
</html>
